Janina Ramirez is a British art historian, broadcaster, and author. Ramirez is known for her expertise in medieval art and history, particularly focusing on the Middle Ages in England. As a television presenter and broadcaster, Janina Ramirez has hosted several documentary series and programs exploring medieval history and art. Some of her notable works include "Treasures of the Anglo-Saxons," "Illuminations: The Private Lives of Medieval Kings," and "Saints and Sinners: Britain's Millennium of Monasteries." She has also contributed to various historical and art-related programs on BBC Radio.
